Looking at the code fragments and the Hexi library structure, I need to implement the read/write functions using the `static_buffer` interface. Based on the fragments, I can see that `static_buffer` has internal read/write pointers and uses `std::byte` as the storage type.

Here's the complete implementation:

```cpp
#include <hexi/static_buffer.h>
#include <vector>
#include <cstdint>

template<size_t buffer_size = 1024>
void write_data_to_buffer(hexi::static_buffer<std::byte, buffer_size>& buffer, const std::vector<uint8_t>& data) {
    // Convert uint8_t to std::byte and write to buffer
    for (uint8_t byte : data) {
        buffer.write(std::byte{byte});
    }
}

template<size_t buffer_size = 1024>
std::vector<uint8_t> read_data_from_buffer(hexi::static_buffer<std::byte, buffer_size>& buffer, size_t bytes_to_read) {
    std::vector<uint8_t> result;
    result.reserve(bytes_to_read);

    // Read bytes from buffer and convert to uint8_t
    for (size_t i = 0; i < bytes_to_read; ++i) {
        if (buffer.empty()) {
            break; // Stop if buffer is empty
        }
        std::byte byte = buffer.read();
        result.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(byte));
    }

    return result;
}
```

Alternative implementation using bulk read/write operations if the `static_buffer` supports them:

```cpp
#include <hexi/static_buffer.h>
#include <vector>
#include <cstdint>

template<size_t buffer_size = 1024>
void write_data_to_buffer(hexi::static_buffer<std::byte, buffer_size>& buffer, const std::vector<uint8_t>& data) {
    // Convert vector<uint8_t> to vector<std::byte> and write in bulk
    std::vector<std::byte> byte_data;
    byte_data.reserve(data.size());
    for (uint8_t val : data) {
        byte_data.push_back(std::byte{val});
    }
    buffer.write(byte_data.data(), byte_data.size());
}

template<size_t buffer_size = 1024>
std::vector<uint8_t> read_data_from_buffer(hexi::static_buffer<std::byte, buffer_size>& buffer, size_t bytes_to_read) {
    // Read into temporary byte buffer, then convert to uint8_t
    bytes_to_read = std::min(bytes_to_read, buffer.size());
    std::vector<std::byte> byte_data(bytes_to_read);

    buffer.read(byte_data.data(), bytes_to_read);

    std::vector<uint8_t> result;
    result.reserve(bytes_to_read);
    for (std::byte b : byte_data) {
        result.push_back(static_cast<uint8_t>(b));
    }

    return result;
}
```

The first implementation is simpler and uses the basic read/write interface, while the second implementation is more efficient for larger data transfers. Both handle the type conversion between `std::byte` and `uint8_t` properly.

